ξ 17. Manumission was either a public or a private act. When manumission, besides freeing a slave from the dominion of his pro- prietor‚ converted him into a citizen of Rome, it was not a matter of merely private interest to be accomplished by the sole volition of the proprietor. Accordingly, the three modes of manumission which conferred the Roman franchise on the manumitted slave, testamento, censu, vindicta, involved in different forms the inter- vention of the State.
